Day 8 -  At the start of today's practice, I was thinking oh this is impossible - and by end of day 8, it turned out:  I"m Possible!  Anything is Possible! Yahoo!!!! 

Pigeon Pose experience: Super tight hips, body is saying "woah, yikes...did we have a muscle in this spot?", Adriene is reminding me to BREATHE into it. I look back at my foot and say "One Day". But something in my says TRY...I bend my knee and reach for my foot, don't make it, but try again and again, breathe deep, connect the mind and body - AND THEN 1 second I touched my right foot!! (WHAT? I can't believe this!!)

Crow Pose: Super tough, that deep squat is very difficult for me. I"m sitting on a two blocks cuz i'm no where near the ground yet. I leaned forward and fell on my head, my knees were digging into my arms and it kinda hurts, I lifted on foot but was too afraid to try to lift the 2nd foot. But i didn't not come on this journey to be afraid, i came here to try....so I did - again and again and again...for about 1 second I had both feet off the ground. (Who Am I? I feel so empowered!)

The first part of this practice reminded me of my time living in India, where I had to learn to use squat toilets; being born and raised in the U.S, this was such a crazy humiliating and painful experience that I had to journal about it! But this practice brought back the good memories and that I can do it again. Then, I felt like JCVD training in Bloodsport with the ropes extensions and had the soundtrack playing in my head. Hahaha, so I dedicate that part of the practice to JCVD. And the third? Holy moly, I had a profound existential experience. And to top off my confusing emotions of joy and sadness, the video ended and the next one started playing of 8 hours of ASMR rain drop sound effects and I was mind blown. The most gratitude for this practice teacher Adriene, and to everyone supportive in the comments!!
